  "text": "The laser and cameras were mounted to a linear motion traverse which could attain any streamwise position while maintaining alignment. The side-view was assembled from three camera images that combine to form a 25.5 cm field of view (5 slot lengths, L) beginning at the leading edge of the generating injection slot. Using a calibration plate, the side-view images were dewarped with a 3rd order polynomial fit to eliminate perspective distortions. [CITATION_1] Side-view PIV planes were recorded with a 19 pix/mm magnification which yielded 2.4 vectors/mm. End-view PIV data were recorded with a camera and a 45",
